DRIVERS
1. Nvidia Driver. (should be already installed by supplier)
2. Nvidia CUDA & CuDNN. Follow https://medium.com/@zhanwenchen/install-cuda-and-cudnn-for-tensorflow-gpu-on-ubuntu-79306e4ac04e

GIT
1. Install git.
2. Clone the FIT repo. git clone -b KU_dev https://scm.fit.fraunhofer.de/scm/git/monica

MYSQL
1. Install mysql, with username root and password root (TODO: THIS SHOULD BE MORE SECURE).
2. Start the service and ensure it starts on boot
3. Run DB initialisation. mysql -u root -p < monica/WP5/KU/SecurityFusionNodeService/SecurityFusionNode/mysql_setup_db.sql

SCRAL CHECK
1. Check connect to SCRAL. curl 'http://monappdwp3.monica-cloud.eu:8000/scral/sfn'


DOCKER
1. install Docker CE. Follow https://docs.docker.com/install/linux/docker-ce/ubuntu/
2. build docker SFN image. sudo docker build -f Dockerfile_sfn -t sfn .
3. Run the Docker Image. sudo docker run --net="host" -t sfn
4. Test with sfn_http_request.py
-. stop the docker Image. sudo docker stop $(sudo docker ps -q --filter ancestor=sfn)

TEST ALGORITHMS WORK


RUNNING KU DEPLOYMENT TOOL



